Name: Glengariff Dr & Louth Rd, Floreat
Description: After living in Floreat for over 26 years I avoid this intersection at all costs. Traffic heading East down Glengariff Dr turning right on to Louth Rd will continually cut the corner and risk having a head on collision. The intersection is very wide and has no medium strip which allows this to happen.

Name: 65, Floreat
Description: If you are travelling north/south and want to turn left right, there are so many close calls and accidents. It is a very busy intersection. It was fixed the other way with arrows why not the whole intersection!
Comment 3: Neville: Travelling South on Brookdale intending to make a right turn into Underwood at the traffic lights. There is no right turn arrow and it is difficult to identify if cars are traveling North or turning into Underwood to travel East. Sometimes only the front car may be signaling and others intending to go ahead. Very congested at school closing times.  Also a problem at school closing times at exit from Forum shops as children riding bikes on the footpath and cars entering and leaving.
Comment 6: Vehicles travelling south down Brockway Road have little chance to turn right into Underwood Ave because of lack of a right turn phase in the traffic lights and heavy traffic in the opposite direction obstructing the view of the driver.

Name: 116 Lissadell St, Floreat
Description: Cars turning right out of Seymour Ave onto The Boulevard rarely give way to cars turning left out of Lissadell. Even though they are a continuation of the same street, the cars turning in front of oncoming traffic think they have the right of way. Many accidents and near misses here. Maybe needs a roundabout?

Name: 72, Floreat
Main Risk: Vehicles travel over the speed limit
Risk Second: Poor or no provision for cyclists
Description: During peak hour, traffic travelling east on The Boulevard approach this roundabout at high speed making it difficult for vehicles to enter the roundabout safely from Grantham Street. This causes traffic build up. When there is a small opportunity to enter the roundabout it is necessary to do so with speed as even though there is no vehicle already in the roundabout traffic approaching are barely slowing down on approach.
